What did I do :)

Notes on my decks:
 - Sasaya, 7 lands in hand flipper -- deck is terrible (i could make it better for sure) and i didn't find it fun at all, going to take it down to make room for other decks asap. Not going to waste time thinking of upgrades.

 - Chainer -- did well the couple of times i had the guts to pull it out in public. Got foil ransack the lab (which is really good). I'm very pleased by removing the handstax portion of the deck. I got owned by a Karrthus which makes me think I need more instant speed removal, or maybe i shouldnt have been greedy and have tutored for a maze of ith instead. Either way, i'm going to try to put 4-5 pieces of instant speed removal in the deck. I'm on the fence about trying out the Rings of Brighthearth for the fetchland doubling... need to see what other activated abilities I've got.

 - Niv Mizzet Parun -- did good and thought it was fun, got some good feedback from Cameron from Lab Maniacs, mostly on some good things to cut. Mostly bad counterspells and some of my slower mana rocks. Going to add Pyretic Ritual and its friend to ramp out.  I want to add more red boardwipes (subterranean tremors, earthquake, perhaps some others) spot removal instead of some of the weaker counterspells. Got an Alpha Red Elemental Blast, which is sweeeet.

 - Grenzo Goblins -- had a decent time playing this deck but I think it's time to take it apart. I felt like usually when I played it I was an underdog in most situations. A bunch of 1/1s just dont do much in today's format. Its fun to cast other peoples spells but i never really did anything that explosive. I like the deck but I think it's time to retire this guy and maybe move onto Goad Cat, but I'm not sure yet. The other idea I had was Palashik Mons big red control. The couple of times I got this dude out with a bunch of mana he made a TON of value. Either way not going to spend time thinking about cuts/additions of the current iteration and will probably figure out the Sasaya replacement first.

 - Kethis Combat Legends -- by far the deck I played the most and enjoyed the most. felt like it was powerful, resilient and good... but still pretty fair i think (?). Changes that need to be made to the deck:
   - get rid of the things that I thought were going to do good combat damage early on and that's the only value they have. The GW legend that has p/t equal to the number of creatures is a good example of this. The deck just isn't fast enough to want to aggro down.
   - I need more spot removal and board wipes. I was against it because i wanted to pack in as many legendaries as possible for aggro reasons but sometimes I reached boardstates I couldn't attack through. Basically, the deck's not fast enough to burst down players so I need to be able to deal more with lategame threats so that I can punch through. Henry turned me onto Slaughter The Strong -- that card is bonkers in my deck. Kethis can live and then recast everything. I'm going to look at a few other boardwipes like that and maybe just add Wrath of God as insurance. The deck has a pretty easy time recovering. Adding things like Anguished Unmaking, StP, Path of Exile, Merciless Eviction, Slaughter the Strong.
  - I'm going to look into the interaction of animating lands to be creatures, since i can animate legendary lands and they get the legendary bonuses my other guys like Arvad the Cursed are giving. Maybe some of the nissa planeswalkers, maybe some awaken stuff, not sure yet. Need to hit the scryfall.
  - Really not sure about removing Bolas Citadel but I need to consider it. Shit is so good when I get it but I ended up killing myself with shit like Avacyn and Elesh Norn.
